{"questionId":"22306295","questionHtml":"<p>Find the smallest positive integer, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi></math>, for which <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>z</mi><mi>n</mi></msup></math> is real and positive.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>8</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Since <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mi>n</mi></mrow><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math> must be a multiple of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></math>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><strong><em>[1 mark]</em></strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22306295","referenceCode":"24M.1.AHL.TZ2.15c","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find the smallest positive integer, n, for which zn is real and positive.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.12—Complex numbers introduction","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.13—Polar and Euler form"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}